y: none !important;"></div><p>Clay shrinkage is my biggest enemy at the mom=
ent. I=E2=80=99ll make an AWESOME, HUGE mug, thinking it will at least be 1=
0 oz, and it turns out to be a very normal 8 oz size. So, if you=E2=80=99ve=
 ever been puzzled by how much your clay piece shrinks after firing, you=E2=
=80=99re not alone. But, we have good news! I explained my constant dilemma=
 to my dad, and he created our handy clay shrinkage calculator. It=E2=80=99=
s a simple tool to help you figure out the right size to start with, so you=
r finished piece turns out just how you want it. And we=E2=80=99re sharing =
it for free!</p><p><a href=3D"https://potterybeginners.com/never-guess-agai=
n-the-clay-shrinkage-calculator-every-potter-needs/#calculator">Jump to the=
