-3-color has-alpha-channel-opacity has-mono-3-background-color has-backgrou=
nd is-style-wide"><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-primary-color has-text-=
color has-link-color wp-elements-f40ef3ccd2c897781cd6b4cfa77bd8e6"><strong>=
The Science Behind the Shrink</strong></h2><p>When you fire clay, it typica=
lly shrinks between 5% and 20%. Why does this happen? As clay dries and fir=
es, it loses water and undergoes physical and chemical changes. Here are a =
few things that influence shrinkage:&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Type of Clay:</str=
ong> Different types of clay, such as earthenware, stoneware, and porcelain=
, have varying shrinkage rates due to their unique compositions.</p><ul cla=
ss=3D"wp-block-list"><li>Earthenware: typical shrinkage rate of around 5% t=
o 8%</li>

<li>Stoneware: typical shrinkage rate of around 10% to 12%</li>

<li>Porcelain: typical shrinkage rate of around 12% to 15%</li></ul><p><str=
ong>Drying Process: </strong>The rate and duration of drying can affect the=
 amount of shrinkage. Faster drying can lead to more shrinkage.</p><p><stro=
ng>Firing Temperature: </strong>&nbsp;The higher the firing temperature, th=
e more the clay shrinks. However, after reaching a certain point, the clay =
swells before eventually melting.</p><hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-te=
xt-color has-mono-3-color has-alpha-channel-opacity has-mono-3-background-c=
olor has-background is-style-wide"><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-primar=
y-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-e480671473caae73a3d1d1c60=
1d83a97"><strong>Accuracy Matters</strong></h2><p>Getting your measurements=
 right is crucial in pottery. A small error in sizing can lead to a big dif=
ference in your final piece. Knowing your clay=E2=80=99s shrinkage percenta=
ge and using a clay shrinkage calculator can save you from potential disapp=
ointments!</p><hr class=3D"wp-block-separator has-text-color has-mono-3-col=
or has-alpha-channel-opacity has-mono-3-background-color has-background is-=
style-wide"><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading has-primary-color has-text-color =
has-link-color wp-elements-2611c25932f4ed06408e6cf2e98349a6" id=3D"calculat=
or"><strong><strong>Why Our Clay Shrinkage Calculator Rocks</strong></stron=
g></h2><p>Our calculator is here to take the guesswork out of your pottery =
projects. Just pop in your project details, hit calculate, and you=E2=80=99=
ll know the perfect starting size to achieve your desired final dimensions.=
</p>


